comment: Very light. Very smooth. Doesn't taste like most bourbons. Compliments Cuban cigars very well.

Best bourbon I’ve had. Lots of great flavors, just the right amount of burn. Has a great cigar box tobacco note to it, I had a Single barrel reserve, hand selected by Jonathon Maisano for Maisano’s in Ocean Springs, MS.
smooth and strong.  oaky with not a lot of burn.  While it does taste heavier than many standard bourbons, for a cask strength it doesn't pack that "punch in the mouth" potency and is very smooth
Poor flavor and terrible finish, probably use it to make vanilla extract.
